        <sect1>
            <title>House of Erwin</title>

            <para>
                This is actually the parent House of House Aethlfryth.
                It is closely allied with that House, and supports it
                in every way possible. This loyalty has meant the
                House has amassed large amounts of lands around its
                ancestral home lands of <qv uri="merrik-shire">Merrik</qv>.
            </para>

            <para>
                The Ealdorman of the House is Madog son of Cadwallon. He
                is a capable merchant and politician, though not a warrior,
                and there is some friction in the house between him and
                those who would prefer a more warrior orientated leadership.
                His brother Cadthar is the focus of this other group.
                Cadthar is a hero of the Cadwold wars, and greatly
                respected by the House's warriors.
            </para>

            <sect2>
                <title>Nobles of House Erwin</title>

                <para>
                    Members of this house tend to be highly politically
                    motivated, and somewhat conservative in their beliefs.
                    They like the status quo, and will generally try not to
                    get involved unless doing so is absolutely necessary.
                </para>

                <para>
                    There is a small but growing faction within the House
                    that believes it is a warrior's job to rule, and
                    would prefer to drop the politics and concentrate
                    on the military strength of the House. Since there
                    isn't actually an enemy to fight, they are having
                    a hard time convincing the rest of the House.
                </para>

                <character name="Ealdorman Madog">
                    <description>
                        <gender>Male</gender>
                        <age>53</age>
                        <short>A short greying man who is quite handsome</short>

                        <physical>
                            <para>
                                Madog is a short man with grey hair. He
                                is always well dressed, and is charming
                                and sociable. He is of average build but
                                not very fit.
                            </para>
                        </physical>
                    </description>
                </character>
                
