        <sect1>
            <title>Characters</title>
            
            <para>
                Characters of this House tend to be highly politically
                motivated, with a large number of connections to the
                powers that be across the Kingdom. However, the status
                quo is good to them, and they tend to be conservative
                in their beliefs and careful in their actions.
            </para>
            
            <para>
                Because they are near the top of the social heirarchy,
                there are always those willing to see them fall, and to
                help them in doing so if the opportunity arises.
            </para>
            
            <sect2>
                <title>Advantages</title>
                
                <advantages role="background" title="House of Erwin">
                    
                    <advantage name="House of Erwin" type="background">
                        <cost points="10"/>
                        
                        <description>
                            <para>
                                The character is a member of the great
                                noble house of Erwin. The House is rich
                                and powerful, and the character will have
                                some access to this wealth.
                            </para>
                        </description>
                    </advantage>

                    <advantage name="Access to Wealth" type="background">
                        <cost points="3"/>
                        <prerequisite>House of Erwin</prerequisite>
                        
                        <description>
                            <para>
                                The character has access to money beyond
                                what she herself actually owns, probably
                                from generous relations. The character's
                                wealth level is increased by one, though
                                the extra funds have to be asked for.
                            </para>
                        </description>
                    </advantage>
                    
                    <advantage name="Political Sense" type="background">
                        <cost points="2"/>
                        <prerequisite>House of Erwin</prerequisite>
                        
                        <description>
                            <para>
                                The character has been instilled with lots
                                of common sense regarding politics. Any
                                time the player chooses to do something
                                that may be 'disruptive', the GM should
                                warn them and give them a chance to
                                rethink. This House breeds conformity.
                            </para>
                        </description>
                    </advantage>
                    
                    <advantage name="Aura of Reason" type="background">
                        <cost points="3"/>
                        <prerequisite>House of Erwin</prerequisite>
                        
                        <description>
                            <para>
                                The character comes across as reasonable
                                and balanced. Whenever they are trying to
                                calm a situation or point forward a
                                reasonable point of view, they gain +1 to
                                their charisma.
                            </para>
                        </description>
                    </advantage>
                </advantages>
            </sect2>
        </sect1>
